3. Protocol implementations & public specifications
---------------------------------------------------

sluice's protocol code is an independent implementation that follows PUBLIC
specifications. The specifications themselves are the work of their respective
authors; following a public spec does not transfer sluice's MIT License to those
specs:

  - NIP-44 (versioned encryption, v2) — https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/44.md
  - NIP-47 / Nostr Wallet Connect (NWC)  — https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/47.md
  - NIP-01 (basic protocol / event format) — https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/01.md
  - BOLT #11 (Lightning invoice format) — https://github.com/lightning/bolts/blob/master/11-payment-encoding.md

The NIP-44 v2 conformance tests in this repository exercise the OFFICIAL NIP-44 v2
test vectors published with the NIP-44 specification:

    https://github.com/nostr-protocol/nips/blob/master/44.md
    Vectors: https://github.com/paulmillr/nip44 (official NIP-44 v2 test vectors)

Credit for those vectors goes to the NIP-44 specification authors and maintainers.
They are used here solely to verify spec conformance.
